Hands-on networking lab covering TCP communication, port scanning, and network service discovery using netcat and nmap across enterprise-scale networks.

üöÄ Lab Overview
This repository contains solutions and documentation for CSCI 400 Lab 11, focusing on network communication fundamentals, port scanning techniques, and service discovery in complex network environments.

üîç Challenge Categories
Basic TCP Communication - Netcat connectivity and data transmission

Network Service Interaction - Sending and receiving data through sockets

Port Listening - Setting up network listeners and service endpoints

Network Scanning - Discovering services across subnets and large IP ranges

Advanced Scanning Techniques - Optimized nmap scans for efficiency

üõ†Ô∏è Skills Demonstrated
bash
# Basic netcat communication
nc 10.0.0.2 31337

# Network listening
nc -l -p 31337

# Port scanning with nmap
nmap -p 31337 10.0.0.0/24 -Pn --open

# Advanced scanning
nmap -p 31337 10.0.0.0/18 -T5 --min-rate 5000
TCP Socket Programming - Raw network communication with netcat

Port Scanning Methodology - Systematic network service discovery

Subnet Navigation - Scanning across CIDR ranges (/24, /18)

Network Service Identification - Detecting and connecting to open ports

Scan Optimization - Using timing templates and rate limiting

Enterprise Network Reconnaissance - Large-scale network exploration

